Package: GPCCA
Type: Package
Title: Generalized Probabilistic Canonical Correlation Analysis
Version: 1.0
Date: 2025-08-15
Authors@R: c(
    person("Tianjian", "Yang", email = "tyang115@ucr.edu", role = c("aut", "cre")),
    person("Wei Vivian", "Li", email = "weil@ucr.edu", role = c("aut", "cph")))
Maintainer: Tianjian Yang <tyang115@ucr.edu>
Description: Implementation of Generalized Probabilistic Canonical Correlation 
  Analysis (GPCCA) on multi-modal dataset. GPCCA is a probabilistic framework 
  built on Gaussian latent variable model, serving as an extension of the 
  classic probabilistic CCA (PCCA), and it generalizes PCCA from two to more 
  than two modalities. GPCCA can handle incomplete data with various patterns 
  of missing values.
License: GPL (>= 3)
Encoding: UTF-8
Depends: R (>= 4.0)
Imports: Rcpp (>= 1.0), stats, MASS, dplyr, Matrix, rsvd, pcaMethods, randcorr, 
  Seurat, diceR, parallel, rstan
Suggests: pdfCluster, umap, ggplot2, knitr, rmarkdown
LinkingTo: Rcpp, RcppArmadillo
URL: https://github.com/Kaversoniano/GPCCA
